				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Games with outlined graphics will look less different, because this lessens the impact of NTSC limitations. I've encountered this issue connecting a SNES to my TV via S-Video versus composite; games like Super Mario World, Zelda: A Link to the Past, and Super Mario Kart look great with S-Video, while things like Donkey Kong Country look poor due to the pixel perfect image, but good with composite. Like you say, attempts at gradients and texturing look better with composite, because it adds more variation and texture, while S-Video or RGB exposes the limited number of colors of the system too much.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

