				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">A lot of Genesis games use an odd dithering technique consisting of vertical lines, rather than the usual dot pattern, because an NTSC TV will blend the lines together (though I don't know about Toy Story, never played it). Ristar makes use of this in combination with shadow mode on the map screen, and Sonic 2 uses it in Chemical Plant Zone to simulate "transparent" tubes.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><strong>- BMF</strong>
